cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper discusses practical recommendations for training deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning research. The focus on gradient-based optimization and back-propagation suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. However, the use of neural networks for computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) also make these sub-categories likely. Additionally, the mention of "deep architectures" suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be relevant.
